Title: Release v1.0.0 — Scroll of Universal Respect

Description
This release formalizes the Scroll of Universal Respect 1.0: a canonical teaching scroll, a machine‑readable policy, and a lightweight enforcement library to embed consent and boundary protections into human‑shaped interactions. It includes policy, enforcement code, tests, CI, and documentation to ensure lineage‑safe behavior and auditable enforcement.

Highlights
- docs/scroll-of-universal-respect.md canonical teaching scroll
- policy/universal-respect.policy.json machine‑readable default‑deny policy
- src/respect_guard/ enforcement library with consent tokens and logging
- examples/demo.py usage examples and smoke tests
- tests/ unit tests and CI workflow

Release Notes
- Enforces default‑deny for private zones and explicit consent for sensitive zones
- Logs all consent events and violations for auditability
- CI configured to run tests on push and PRs
- Security and contribution guidance added to repo

